</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-3.4)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img3_q4.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Bicycle</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">What do bicycles mean to you?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> What do bicycles mean to you?
Bài làm: 
childhood memories 
-> freedom and peaceful.
Bicycle is particularly meaningful to me. In the past, when i used to be a child, my family was really poor, my mom gave me a bicycle as a gift on my 6 birthday. At firts, i was scared because it was so hard, i kept falling over and over but  to control the bike i practiced a lot and finally mastered it. This bring about the sense of achievement, freedom. Overtime, i am mature now, i use the motorbike instead, however, i still store my old bike in garage because when i look at it remind me of my childhood.     </p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.1)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q1.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Book</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">What kinds of things do you enjoy reading in English?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> What kinds of things do you enjoy reading in English ?.
I really reading English vocab books. It enhances my vocab ranges, and i can learn the vocab properly according to the situations. Sometimes, i also read the newspaper in English. It provides information on what it is happening in the world like the virrus named Nipah from India, it is infectious and deadly diseases derived from local fruit bat, ... I think people and government should be careful with it. 
</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.2)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q2.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Book</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">Do you have a favorite place to read?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Do you have a favorite place to read?
My favourite place is at the library in school. Not only the atmosphere in the library is peaceful, but i also can meet like-minded people. This helps me to concentrate and stay motivated. 
Sometimes, i go the caffee shop with friends. We can exchange and share the book content. 
</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.3)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q3.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
