                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Do you need peace and quiet to be able to read?
Because when i have a lot of assignments so i need peaceful atmosphere to concentrate 100% on the books. The noise makes me feel distracted and annoyed. 
</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.4)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q4.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Book</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">How did you first learn to read?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> How did you first learn to read ?.
-> Cảm xúc ban đầu -> quá trình  _phonics___. thanks to my teacher _diễn biến____. -> __bài học___. 
make fun of me: lấy làm trò cười.
I remember that when i used to be a child, in my kindergarden school, 
my teacher asked me to read out phonics. I was really shy and anxious because my classmates made fun of me. But my teacher patiently helped me to practise until i read correctly. From this experience, i realized that people can make mistakes but it is important to overcome them and move forward. </p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.5)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q5.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Book</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">What did you prefer reading as a child?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> What did you prefer reading as a child?
-> I really enjoyed picture books. -> Fairy tales (cổ tích) were my favorite. 
+) happy ending -> more hope in life.-> it teach me good people will have a good life. 
+) colour (eye-catching) -> keep me at the edge at the seat. 
+) meaningful -> learn a lot from it.</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-4.6)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img4_q6.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
                        <div><p class="text-[10px] font-black text-rose-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">IELTS Speaking Part 1 • Book</p><p class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 leading-tight">Has your reading habit changed since you were a child?</p></div>
                    </div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Has your reading habit changed since you were a child?
I shifted from fairy tail to newspaper
fairy tail -> is dreamy, romantic, unrealistic. Some characters are dumb and unpractical. I believe that kindness not always bring about happy ending. 
While, newspaper -> useful -> provide information, global current situations, or sometimes i read English newpaper to enhance English skills....   

</p><hr><h3>Part 7: IELTS Speaking (ID: P7-5.1)</h3><p><div class="glass-card p-6 flex items-center gap-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                        <img src="image/p7_img5_q1.png" class="w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg border-2 border-white" onerror="this.src='data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='400' height='300' viewBox='0 0 400 300'%3E%3Crect width='400' height='300' fill='%2310b981' opacity='0.1'/%3E%3Ctext x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' font-family='Outfit' font-weight='800' font-size='24' fill='%2310b981'%3EPart%207 Stimulus%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E'">
